---
import DevLayout from '../../../layouts/DevLayout.astro';
import ExampleBackToTop from '../../../components/examples/ExampleBackToTop.astro';
---

<DevLayout>
  <ExampleBackToTop />
  <section class="component-info-section py-5">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="mb-3">Example Back to Top Component</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>ExampleBackToTop</strong> is a section component that demonstrates a back-to-top button with smooth scroll functionality. The button appears when users scroll down and provides a smooth scroll back to the top of the page.
      </p>
      
      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="h5 mb-3">Back to Top Features</h3>
          <ul class="mb-0">
            <li>Follows BEM structure and project section conventions</li>
            <li>Section wrapper: <code>page-sec page-sec--example-back-to-top</code> with <code>container</code></li>
            <li>Fixed position button that appears after scrolling 300px</li>
            <li>Smooth scroll animation with proper timing</li>
            <li>Accessible with proper ARIA labels and focus states</li>
            <li>Visual feedback with hover and active states</li>
            <li>Performance optimized with throttled scroll events</li>
            <li>Prevents multiple clicks during scroll animation</li>
            <li>Fully responsive: adapts size and position for mobile</li>
            <li>All styles in dedicated SCSS partial, imported in <code>main.scss</code></li>
            <li>JavaScript functionality in dedicated module</li>
            <li>Ready for use in design system and real site pages</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="h5 mb-3">Usage Examples</h3>
          
          <h6 class="mt-3">Basic Back to Top Button</h6>
          <pre style="background:#f8f8f8;padding:1rem;border-radius:6px;overflow:auto"><code>{`<button class="back-to-top js__example-back-to-top" aria-label="Back to top">
  <svg class="back-to-top__icon" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
    <path d="M12 4L4 12H9V20H15V12H20L12 4Z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>
  <span class="back-to-top__text">Top</span>
</button>`}</code></pre>

          <h6 class="mt-3">Component Usage</h6>
          <pre style="background:#f8f8f8;padding:1rem;border-radius:6px;overflow:auto"><code>{`---
import ExampleBackToTop from '../../../components/examples/ExampleBackToTop.astro';
---
<ExampleBackToTop />`}</code></pre>

          <h6 class="mt-3">Custom Implementation</h6>
          <pre style="background:#f8f8f8;padding:1rem;border-radius:6px;overflow:auto"><code>{`// Add to your page
<button class="back-to-top js__example-back-to-top" aria-label="Back to top">
  <!-- Your custom icon or text -->
  <span>â†‘</span>
</button>

// JavaScript will automatically initialize any element with js__example-back-to-top class`}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="h5 mb-3">Technical Details</h3>
          <ul class="mb-0">
            <li><strong>CSS Classes:</strong> Uses <code>js__example-back-to-top</code> for JavaScript targeting</li>
            <li><strong>Scroll Threshold:</strong> Button appears after scrolling 300px down</li>
            <li><strong>Animation:</strong> Smooth scroll with CSS transitions and hover effects</li>
            <li><strong>Performance:</strong> Throttled scroll events using requestAnimationFrame</li>
            <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Proper ARIA labels, focus states, and keyboard navigation</li>
            <li><strong>JavaScript:</strong> Module-based initialization with scroll detection</li>
            <li><strong>Responsive:</strong> Adapts size and position for different screen sizes</li>
            <li><strong>Brand Colors:</strong> Uses brand blue (#0099f7) with hover states</li>
            <li><strong>Z-index:</strong> High z-index (1000) to ensure visibility</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DevLayout> 